.TH "i915_oa_stream_enable" 9 "i915_oa_stream_enable" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
i915_oa_stream_enable \- handle `I915_PERF_IOCTL_ENABLE` for OA stream
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" i915_oa_stream_enable
.BI "(struct i915_perf_stream *stream "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "stream" 12
An i915 perf stream opened for OA metrics
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
[Re]enables hardware periodic sampling according to the period configured
when opening the stream. This also starts a hrtimer that will periodically
check for data in the circular OA buffer for notifying userspace (e.g.
during a \fBread\fP or \fBpoll\fP).
